messages.ssml: <speak>CDC has not received any reports of pets becoming sick with <sub alias="covid 19">COVID-19</sub> in the United States, though it is aware of a very small number of pets, including dogs and cats, reported to be infected with the virus outside of the U.S. To date, there is no evidence that pets can spread the virus to people though it is still recommended that people sick with <sub alias="covid 19">COVID-19</sub> limit contact with animals until more information is known about the new coronavirus. When possible, have another member of your household care for your animals while you are sick.</speak>
